verbose_text: Another possible level of regulation of NF-kappaB by optineurin is through ubiquitin binding domain (UBD)-dependent binding to trans-activating transcriptional regulatory protein of HTLV-1 (TAX1), which when ubiquitinated binds to NEMO, leading to NF-kappaB activation.
evidence: ubiquitin-binding domain (UBD)-dependent binding to trans-activating transcriptional regulatory protein of HTLV-1 (TAX1), which when ubiquitinated binds to NEMO
